Axiom (mulmnone):
  for all v0, (if v0 is an object then (- 1 \cdot v0 is equal to - v0 and - v0 is equal to v0 \cdot - 1))

Theorem (mulzero):
  for all v0, (if v0 is an object then (v0 \cdot 0 is equal to 0 and 0 is equal to 0 \cdot v0))
Proof:
  x \cdot 0 is equal to 0
  Proof:
    x \cdot 0 is equal to x \cdot 0 + x \cdot 0
    Proof:
      x \cdot 0 is equal to x \cdot 0 + 0
      x \cdot 0 + 0 is equal to x \cdot 0 + x \cdot 0
    Qed.
  Qed.
  0 \cdot x is equal to 0
  Proof:
    0 \cdot x is equal to 0 \cdot x + 0 \cdot x
    Proof:
      0 \cdot x is equal to 0 + 0 \cdot x
      0 + 0 \cdot x is equal to 0 \cdot x + 0 \cdot x
    Qed.
  Qed.
Qed.

Axiom (cancel):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an object and v1 is an object then (if it is wrong that (v0 is equal to 0) and it is wrong that (v1 is equal to 0) then it is wrong that (v0 \cdot v1 is equal to 0))))

Axiom (unnezr):
  it is wrong that (1 is equal to 0)

Axiom:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a set then for all v1, (if v1 is an element of v0 then v1 is an object))

Axiom (seteq):
