Theorem (prideal):
  for all v0, (if v0 is an object then \langle v0 \rangle is an ideal)
Proof:
  x is an element of \langle c \rangle
  for all v0, (if v0 is an element of \langle c \rangle then x + v0 is an element of \langle c \rangle)
  Proof:
    y is an element of \langle c \rangle
    u is an object and c \cdot u is equal to x
    v is an object and c \cdot v is equal to y
    x + y is equal to c \cdot u + v
    Proof:
      x + y is equal to c \cdot u + v
    Qed.
    the thesis holds
  Qed.
  for all v0, (if v0 is an object then v0 \cdot x is an element of \langle c \rangle)
  Proof:
    z is an object
    u is an object and c \cdot u is equal to x
    z \cdot x is equal to c \cdot u \cdot z
    Proof:
      z \cdot x is equal to c \cdot u \cdot z
    Qed.
    the thesis holds
  Qed.
Qed.

